From 35af7358a1abf7144dced51b216ea2b6c53e76de Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Francesco Pham <francesco.pham1@h-partners.com>
Date: Thu, 28 May 2026 12:00:37 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] asmjit: integrate panda ArenaAllocator and broaden
 warning suppression

Route asmjit allocations through the parent compiler's ark::ArenaAllocator instead of plain malloc/free so codegen memory follows the encoder's lifetime (the old ::free in static destructors leaked when the encoder was reused).

Also drop -Wunused-parameter / -Wnested-anon-types / -Wgnu-anonymous-struct / -Wpedantic via the begin/end-namespace pragma macros (clang, gcc>=8, and gcc7 branches) so upstream sources compile under the OH compile-standard, and fix ASMJIT_NONCOPYABLE on template classes (drop the angle-bracketed template args from the macro argument).

Signed-off-by: Francesco Pham <francesco.pham1@h-partners.com>
